{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The real failure boundary is between PR-change discovery and file-selection/execution. A unit test of the filter logic can pass while wiring mistakes (wrong path normalization, wrong diff source, stale merge-base handling) still cause unchanged files to be scanned.","test_description":"Run the pipeline logic with a temporary repo fixture plus a synthetic PR changed-file list from the change-provider module, execute analysis end-to-end through file-discovery -> selection -> linter invocation, and assert only changed paths are invoked. Include tricky paths (renames, deleted files, nested dirs) to catch module-boundary mismatches.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Grouping correctness can fail at the handoff between rule outputs, aggregation, and comment rendering/post payload construction. Unit tests on formatter alone may miss schema mismatches or dropped buckets in the integrated comment body.","test_description":"Feed multi-severity findings through the real aggregation + comment-builder path and intercept the final PR-comment payload before network send. Assert sections exist for error/warning/info and findings are placed in correct buckets with stable ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a runtime/SLA behavior tied to process execution, filesystem IO, CPU contention, and Action-like environment limits. Mocked timing or isolated units can hide real timeout failures.","test_description":"Execute the linter step as a real process on a 200-file fixture in CI-equivalent conditions (same runner class/container limits), measure wall-clock end-to-end duration including file discovery and comment payload generation, and fail if >=10 minutes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior explicitly depends on subprocess crash handling and recovery. In-process mocks often turn crashes into exceptions and can miss real exit-code/signal handling and worker-supervision bugs.","test_description":"Run analysis with the real linter subprocess against a corpus containing one crash-inducing malformed file plus valid files. Assert the orchestrator records the crash, continues analyzing remaining files, and still emits/post-builds final findings output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The core failure is deterministic merge/dedup logic on finding keys (file, line, rule/signature). No real IO or module boundary is required to expose incorrect dedup behavior.","test_description":"Test the dedup function/object directly with crafted overlapping findings (same file/line with different rule IDs, same rule emitted twice, near-duplicate messages) and assert only intended unique entries remain per dedup policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.84,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}}]}
